"22:59:6" : {s: 22, a: 59, w: 6, r: "علم", t: "لَعَلِيمٌ", l: "عَلِيم", lc: 163, tl: "laʿalīmun", lb: "পরম জ্ঞানী",e: "surely, (is) All-Knowing", b: "সুবিজ্ঞ", i: "sungguh Maha Mengetahui", f: 1, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows.", ag: "لام التوكيد وأسم نكرة", eg: "Emphatic lām and Noun Indefinite state", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "INDEF", qual: "NOM", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "أَعْلَمُ،عَلِمَ،عَلِيمٌۢ"},
